        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the most important factor when choosing a medspa?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Physician supervision is the single most important factor. You should ask who the medical director is, their board certification and specialty, and how involved they are in patient care on a daily basis. A physician-supervised medspa provides a higher standard of safety and clinical oversight compared to facilities where physician involvement is primarily administrative. At Rani Beauty Clinic, Dr. Alexander Landfield, a board-certified neurologist, actively oversees all medical treatments."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How can I evaluate the quality of a medspa's technology?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Ask about the specific devices and brands the medspa uses, then research those systems. Premium, FDA-cleared devices from established manufacturers generally deliver better results, greater safety, and more patient comfort than lower-cost alternatives. For example, the Candela GentleMax Pro Plus used at Rani Beauty Clinic is a gold-standard laser platform with dual wavelengths and patented cooling technology, the same caliber found in top dermatology and plastic surgery practices."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Why are consultations important before medspa treatments?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Consultations serve as a clinical evaluation to ensure recommended treatments are appropriate and safe for your individual needs. They should include a thorough assessment of your concerns, medical history review, explanation of treatment options, discussion of realistic expectations, and time for your questions. Be cautious of facilities that pressure you to commit to treatment without a proper consultation or that do not take the time to understand your unique goals and health profile."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Should a medspa offer blood work for medical treatments?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes, if a medspa offers medical treatments like GLP-1 weight management, peptide therapy, or NAD+ injections, they should have the capability to perform and monitor blood work. These treatments interact with your body's physiology and require lab monitoring for safety and effectiveness. On-site blood work is a significant advantage, as it streamlines the process and ensures results are integrated promptly into your treatment plan."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What questions should I ask when evaluating a medspa?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Key questions include: Who is the medical director and what is their specialty? How involved is the physician in daily patient care? What specific devices and technology do you use? What are the credentials and training of the injectors and technicians? Can you show before-and-after photos of actual patients? Do you perform blood work on-site for medical treatments? Is a thorough consultation included before any treatment? The right medspa will answer these questions transparently and welcome your inquiry."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
